tion%20I%20don't%20watch%20it%20enough%20to%20make%20it%20worth%20it.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20I%20do%20play%20enough%20solitaire%20on%20my%20phone%20that%20I%20ponied%20up%20for%20the%20ad-free%20version.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProblem%202%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20It's%20a%20trust%20issue.%20Can%20we%20trust%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20give%20%26quot%3Breal%26quot%3B%20answers%20rather%20than%20ads%20when%20we%20ask%20it%20to%20recommend%20a%20product%20or%20service%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20also%20running%20ads%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%2C%20eh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20think%20people%20are%20already%20used%20to%20understanding%20things%20like%20Google%20search%20results%20with%20ads%20where%20there's%20a%20mix%20of%20organic%20and%20sponsored%20results.%20If%20I%20ask%20ChatGPT%20to%20help%20me%20revive%20my%20wilting%20monstera%20plant%2C%20and%20it%20shows%20me%20an%20ad%20for%20Miracle-Gro%20plant%20food%20at%20the%20bottom%2C%20will%20I%20be%20confused%3F%20Probably%20not%20because%20I've%20seen%20this%20kind%20of%20thing%20before%20on%20Google%20and%20social%20feeds.%20The%20mockups%20OpenAI%20shared%20flag%20to%20me%20pretty%20clearly%20what's%20an%20ad%20and%20what%20isn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProblem%203%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20If%20ChatGPT%20is%20in%20the%20advertising%20biz%2C%20then%20it's%20subject%20to%20the%20pressures%20of%20brands%20and%20corporations%20that%20pay%20for%20those%20ads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%2C%20eh%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20OK%2C%20this%20one%20is%20actually%20real.%20Advertisers%20can%20and%20will%20exert%20pressure%20on%20platforms%2C%20broadcasters%2C%20publishers%2C%20and%20any%20other%20venues%20where%20their%20ads%20appear.%20They%20are%20powerful%20in%20that%20way!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20hear%20me%20out%3A%20This%20can%20actually%20have%20a%20kind%20of%20normalizing%20effect%2C%20in%20a%20positive%20way%2C%20especially%20when%20we're%20thinking%20about%20something%20like%20a%20huge%20AI%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%20the%20case%20of%20an%20outlier%20event%3A%20In%202022%2C%20when%20Elon%20Musk%20first%20took%20over%20Twitter%2FX.%20Advertisers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-advertisers-back-again-investors-musk-trump-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efled%20when%20the%20platform%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20deluged%20with%20hateful%20content%2C%20and%20it%20actually%20caused%20X%20to%20have%20to%20change%20its%20ways%20to%20woo%20them%20back.%20When%20we%20consider%20all%20the%20wildly%20terrifying%20things%20that%20a%20platform%20with%20immense%20global%20power%20like%20OpenAI%20can%20do%2C%20it's%20actually%20kind%20of%20a%20good%20thing%20to%20be%20hemmed%20in%20by%20the%20middle-of-the-road%2C%20safe%20values%20and%20standards%20of%20the%20Coca-Cola%20Company%20or%20other%20big%2C%20would-be%20US-based%20advertisers.%20It%20means%20you%20can't%20make%20your%20tech%20product%20so%20problematic%20that%20Walmart%20doesn't%20want%20to%20be%20associated%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProblem%204%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EChatGPT%2C%20a%20wonderful%20product%20that%20operated%20with%20a%20clean%20design%2C%20is%20now%20just%20another%20victim%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcory-doctorow-enshittification-theory-why-tech-social-platforms-go-downhill-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eenshittification%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%2C%20eh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0Buddy%2C%20if%20you're%20a%20huge%20fan%20of%20ChatGPT%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20purity%20of%20the%20beautiful%2C%20human%2C%20internet%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20tell%20you.%20Do%20you%20also%20love%20swimming%2C%20but%20hate%20water%3F%20Pick%20a%20side!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELook%2C%20am%20I%20excited%20to%20have%20one%20more%20place%20to%20be%20annoyed%20by%20ads%3F%20No.%20But%20I%20also%20feel%